data.description:
Your task is to find all possibilities to balance a scale with a number of weights.
The first array tells you the weight on each pan of the scale and the second array contains all the weights you can use to balance the scale.

```scales[0]``` = left pan | ```scales[1]``` = right pan

BUT: You are only allowed to add max. 1 more weight to each pan and the sum of all weights on the scale must not be over 50.

    Example: 
    scales = new int[] { 14, 18 }; 
    weights = new int[] { 1, 4, 8, 12 };

    Solution:
    list = new List<int[]>() { new int[] { 4, 0 }, new int[] { 8, 4 } };

NOTE: Each of your solution must be unique and if it is impossible to balance the scale, just return an empty list.
